ibrary at Nanterre</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_44563b58ed65ce215ae215d3865c4554" level="file"><did><unittitle>PRO - PREM 314 + FO</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1945/1945">1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_5bd94ae1701c255a8d991a69ea97932d" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c512128e20ec90369e19a0019b2b7767" parent="aspace_5bd94ae1701c255a8d991a69ea97932d" type="folder">5-6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_669fb89da0b2e7f65b08d266a15294ea"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Classified documents on French Indo-China from Public Records Office (Foreign Office documents)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_40e26f05a69d014871b2b4106e486296" level="file"><did><unittitle>Mary Speers' Notes</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1942/1943" type="inclusive">1942-1943</unitdate><container id="aspace_0acc3f4f8258f5ab0ae5789507f9734b" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_62f3ccc4cb37537a22a2b7cbf04a6909" parent="aspace_0acc3f4f8258f5ab0ae5789507f9734b" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2fb37c646720f4ad11ac37885ab965b4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Foreign Office series 371/35921, ff. Mostly on wartime relations with France.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_66374441566d62f006507bd57881470f" level="file"><did><unittitle>My Notes 1980 - PRO &amp; Rhodes House</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1980/1980">1980</unitdate><container id="aspace_e4b970fd159531b87d7fb49aab744bd5" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_604df7532198d04ab259513f1608c5dd" parent="aspace_e4b970fd159531b87d7fb49aab744bd5" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_15da68ac1d332fa320352b6d9de99815"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>CAB 121/741 - Notes taken on memos on Indochina for PM from Foreign Section. File: "My Notes 1980: PRO &amp; Roosevelt." CAB 120/56 - 121/741. Succinct notes of heart of documents re: French Indochina (ca. 40-50 pp.). Notebook cover headed "Cabinet Officers etc." has several pages of references to A. Creech Jones.</p><p> 2nd notebook: Rhodes Library Oxford - About 100 pp. of penciled notes on FO 371; CO 824 Register; CO 872-4-9 inclusive (1942, 1942) Mostly to FO 371/371779-90</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_882641775d4bd943c4046cce71f4aac7" level="file"><did><unittitle>DDE '54 - documents</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1954/1954">1954</unitdate><container id="aspace_52a0a89c00540abcd97bfa6f605848c2" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_70b94317741d69dbe07f6d3cdcbeb92a" parent="aspace_52a0a89c00540abcd97bfa6f605848c2" type="folder">9</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_d4c4cd2d8b44f1177511b9a1ffa9da65"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Dwight D. Eisenhower Library</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_42adfae9cae0b88bcf98f8b0bf2e8c14" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives - Use of Indo China Resistance Forces</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1944/1945" type="inclusive">1944-1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_d1cd06532f52ce005e18ee66a48628b6" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_b9bf179c19fbdec699101c5a380ded88" parent="aspace_d1cd06532f52ce005e18ee66a48628b6" type="folder">10-11</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_dbd8f8d86f47433c2d61b3b65e326d31" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1941/1941">1941</unitdate><container id="aspace_d6d5a6e7070c04df34a3a20cd81ae11c" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_806235c37b29213c0521891a31aba655" parent="aspace_d6d5a6e7070c04df34a3a20cd81ae11c" type="folder">12</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_88f942e2113e